In that video, I explained how the World Cup works.

363
00:20:01,218 --> 00:20:04,671
In the midst of these, there is positive news about cricket's popularity

364
00:20:04,671 --> 00:20:08,856
it will soon be included in the Olympics.

365
00:20:08,856 --> 00:20:13,440
This development is expected to introduce the sport to new audiences.

366
00:20:13,440 --> 00:20:16,563
Curiously, cricket's absence from the Olympics until now

367
00:20:16,563 --> 00:20:19,314
can also be attributed to the BCCI's resistance.

368
00:20:22,520 --> 00:20:26,961
One might wonder why the BCCI opposed taking cricket to the Olympics,

369
00:20:26,961 --> 00:20:30,648
given that it would enhance India's chances of winning another gold medal.

370
00:20:30,648 --> 00:20:34,286
The BCCI's objection has consistently centered around the fear

371
00:20:34,286 --> 00:20:36,114
of losing member autonomy

372
00:20:36,114 --> 00:20:38,046
in the face of the International Olympic Committee.

373
00:20:38,046 --> 00:20:43,354
Essentially, a concern that their control over the ICC would be diluted.

374
00:20:43,354 --> 00:20:47,812
With the inclusion of the International Olympic Committee in the equation. 

375
00:20:47,812 --> 00:20:51,854
Deciding match schedules and redistribution of financial costs,

376
00:20:51,854 --> 00:20:54,177
would no longer be within BCCI's purview

377
00:20:54,177 --> 00:20:56,548
once cricket would be played in the Olympics.

378
00:20:56,920 --> 00:20:58,949
In the 2007 cricket World Cup

379
00:20:58,949 --> 00:21:00,620
16 teams had participated.

380
00:21:00,620 --> 00:21:03,037
The was reduced to 14 in 2011,

381
00:21:03,037 --> 00:21:06,173
and further dwindled to 10 teams in 2019.

382
00:21:06,173 --> 00:21:08,274
Do you know why?

383
00:21:08,274 --> 00:21:09,595
Money.

384
00:21:09,595 --> 00:21:13,056
As fewer teams mean more matches for India,

385
00:21:13,056 --> 00:21:17,447
translating into increased revenue for the BCCI.

386
00:21:17,447 --> 00:21:23,275
Not only the BCCI, the England 
Cricket Board (ECB) supported this too. 

387
00:21:23,275 --> 00:21:29,303
The ECB articulated concerns that if cricket 
matches are held for 2-2.5 weeks in the Olympics,

388
00:21:29,303 --> 00:21:31,701
fewer matches would be played in England,

389
00:21:31,701 --> 00:21:34,340
resulting in revenue loss.

390
00:21:34,340 --> 00:21:38,568
However, cricket has been played at the Olympics once.

391
00:21:38,568 --> 00:21:40,493
123 years ago,

392
00:21:40,493 --> 00:21:42,572
in the 1900 Paris Olympics,

393
00:21:42,572 --> 00:21:46,025
where only two cricket teams participated,

394
00:21:46,025 --> 00:21:47,627
and only one match was played.

395
00:21:47,627 --> 00:21:49,689
Between Great Britain and France.

396
00:21:49,689 --> 00:21:54,129
After this, during the 1998 Commonwealth Games in Kuala Lumpur

397
00:21:54,129 --> 00:21:56,847
a full ODI tournament was included.

398
00:21:56,847 --> 00:21:59,361
It had 16 participating teams,

399
00:21:59,361 --> 00:22:03,023
culminated in South Africa winning the gold medal in this tournament.

400
00:22:03,023 --> 00:22:04,521
Australia was in the second spot,

401
00:22:04,521 --> 00:22:06,570
with the silver medal,

402
00:22:06,570 --> 00:22:09,807
when the Australian cricket team captain Steve Waugh had said that

403
00:22:09,807 --> 00:22:13,431
winning that silver medal was the highlight of his career,

404
00:22:13,431 --> 00:22:18,824
even though Steve Waugh had been a part of the World Cup winning team in 1987.

405
00:22:18,824 --> 00:22:21,668
After this, in 2008, during the Beijing Olympics,

406
00:22:21,668 --> 00:22:25,289
he had said that if cricket is to be globalised,

407
00:22:25,289 --> 00:22:29,389
it would mean including countries like China and the USA.

408
00:22:29,389 --> 00:22:33,866
And to include them, the Olympics is the fast-track way.

409
00:22:33,866 --> 00:22:38,564
Australian legendary cricketer Adam Gilchrist echoed these sentiments in 2009,

410
00:22:38,564 --> 00:22:40,830
asserting that making cricket an Olympic sport

411
00:22:40,830 --> 00:22:43,469
would encourage many countries to take the sport seriously

412
00:22:43,469 --> 00:22:45,523
and play it for the first time in their history.

413
00:22:45,523 --> 00:22:48,941
However, no one considered these appeals seriously for so long.

414
00:22:48,941 --> 00:22:51,280
And cricket was kept away from the Olympics.

415
00:22:51,280 --> 00:22:54,084
But now, thankfully, it is changing.

416
00:22:54,084 --> 00:22:57,667
In the upcoming Los Angeles Olympics in 2028,

417
00:22:57,667 --> 00:23:01,132
T20 cricket will finally make its Olympic debut.

418
00:23:01,132 --> 00:23:05,795
This significant decision is influenced by 
the growing popularity of cricket in America.

419
00:23:06,229 --> 00:23:10,027
With the T20 World Cup scheduled to 
be hosted by the United States next year.

420
00:23:10,027 --> 00:23:13,220
By the time cricket makes its Olympic debut, 

421
00:23:13,220 --> 00:23:16,000
Virat Kohli will likely be 40 years old.

422
00:23:16,000 --> 00:23:20,877
The prospect of witnessing whether 
the greatest Indian cricket right now,

423
00:23:20,877 --> 00:23:24,834
can secure an Olympic gold for us or not.

